content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 ยง 346.9 - Chiropractor's fees for hearing purposes

State Regulations
A chiropractor who testifies at hearings or examines
claimants or participates in examination for evidentiary purposes only, without
treatment, may accept fees for such services from the claimant, employer or
carrier requesting the examination. Notes
